  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle, then drain the <strong>tofu</strong> and cut into small bite-sized pieces</p>\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p>\n<p>Once very hot, add the <strong>tofu</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until golden all over</p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-style-tofu-red-pepper-chow-mein/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once done, transfer the <strong>tofu</strong> to kitchen paper and set aside, reserving the pan and oil for later</p>\n<p>Meanwhile, peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>ginger</strong></p>\n<p>Deseed the <strong>red pepper<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p>\n<p>Top, tail, peel and slice the <strong>carrot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into quarters lengthways, then into batons</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-style-tofu-red-pepper-chow-mein/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>wholewheat noodles </strong>to a pot and cover them with <strong>boiled water </strong>until they're fully submerged</p>\n<p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 5-7 min until they're tender with a slight bite</p>\n<p>Once done, drain the <strong>noodles</strong>, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy noodle water</strong></p>\n<p><strong> </strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-style-tofu-red-pepper-chow-mein/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">While the noodles are cooking, comb</span>ine the <strong>hoisin sauce</strong>,<strong> toasted sesame oil</strong>, <strong>chilli jam</strong> and<strong> soy sauce</strong> in a bowl – this is your <strong>chow mein sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-style-tofu-red-pepper-chow-mein/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the pan to a medium heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p>\n<p>Once hot, add the<strong> baby</strong><strong> kale</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until starting to wilt</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>chopped ginger</strong>, <strong>carrot batons </strong>and<strong> </strong><strong>red pepper</strong> to the pan with the <strong>tofu</strong> and cook for 1-2 min, stirring frequently </p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-style-tofu-red-pepper-chow-mein/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chow mein sauce</strong> and <strong>drained noodles</strong> to the pan with a splash of <strong>starchy noodle water</strong> and cook for 1-2 min further, mixing well so that everything's coated in the sauce – this is your <strong>Chinese-style tofu &amp; red pepper chow mein</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-style-tofu-red-pepper-chow-mein/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Trim, then slice the <strong>spring onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> finely</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-style-tofu-red-pepper-chow-mein/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> Chinese-style tofu &amp; red pepper chow mein</strong> and garnish with the <strong>sliced spring onion</strong> and<strong> toasted sesame seeds</strong></p>\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
